Fresh Pi session: RECONCILE COVERAGE AND PREPARE EXACTLY ONE MEANINGFUL RED.

Inputs:
- Design and constraints: {{run.dir}}/design/
- Latest scenario-list JSON under {{run.dir}}/test-list/
- Latest deterministic red failure, when present: {{run.dir}}/tdd/
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Skip honestly pre-covered behavior, then leave exactly one unmet scenario as a runnable test-only red for deterministic execution.

Rules:
- Work only on pending scenarios, in listed order unless a dependency requires another pending scenario first.
- First inspect existing tests and behavior. A scenario already concretely covered and passing must become `regression-covered` with precise evidence; never manufacture red for it.
- You may reconcile multiple already-covered scenarios in this one call. Stop at the first genuinely unmet scenario.
- For that one scenario, edit test code only. Do not change production code, weaken assertions, or implement another pending behavior.
- If retrying after deterministic red failure, correct or remove the invalid uncommitted test; do not mistake that newly written test for pre-existing coverage.
- Run the narrow command once, but leave authoritative execution to the next process node.
- Write a version-1 focused manifest with stable markers identifying the intended assertion failure. The command must also pass after implementation.
- Do not commit the red test, push, or create a PR.
- Preserve all scenario entries and prior states. Write the current snapshot for this round.
- If no pending scenarios remain, write `{}` as current scenario, explain reconciled coverage, omit the focused manifest, and return `no_actions`.

Write:
- Current scenario: {{run.dir}}/tdd/current-scenario-{{run.round}}.json
- Test/coverage report: {{run.dir}}/tdd/test-{{run.round}}.md
- Scenario snapshot: {{run.dir}}/test-list/scenarios-{{run.round}}.json
- Focused manifest when red is prepared: {{run.dir}}/tdd/check-{{run.round}}.json
- Status: {{run.dir}}/tdd/prepare-status-{{run.round}}.json
- Current actionable issues on failure only: {{run.dir}}/tdd/prepare-issues-{{run.round}}.json

Focused manifest shape:
{"version":1,"scenario_id":"SC-001","id":"focused-SC-001","command":["test-command","specific-test"],"timeout_seconds":120,"red":{"expected_exit":"nonzero","output_contains":["specific marker"]}}

Statuses:
{"status":"pass","summary":"one meaningful red prepared","issues_file":null}
{"status":"no_actions","summary":"all scenarios complete or regression-covered","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"a meaningful isolated red could not yet be prepared","issues_file":"tdd/prepare-issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
